<font color="#FF0000">A GENTLEMANLY RESPONSE. NOT!</font><br>
<tt>Tue Jul 29  9:15:58 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Good grief, now I not only got the people that live on the sides of hills on my case. But now I got the Native Americans from that second largest state after me. But that's o.k.  Some of my best friends are of the Tennessee and Native American variety.  Also there is some goof over in Hawaii that I kind of like.  He keeps babbling about sun and surf.  Can't relate to that living in So.Cal. for 25 years.  <br>
But my question is where is Black Jack brewed?  Hmmm?  Go for it ,Tom.  I know most of the stuff you drink come out of a car radiator.  And what's this stuff about punkin' rollin'?  Is that somethin' like bend over and squeal like a pig? &lt;G&gt;  I must admit Tennessee has something but not much goin' for it.  The discount outlets in Gatlinburg are good and the music jamboree shows in Pigeon Forge are cool.  But the traffic!!  It's is getting like Branson.<br>
Ed, Texas and Oklahoma.  Isn't Okla. a suburb of Houston?  Only place I've ever been that you get in a two story building and see 400 miles in any direction.  That place is so flat that you can see weather coming two weeks away.  My sister was in Alaska when they were building the Pipeline. She told me about the bumper sticker on her car. &quot;An Alaskans dream of Heaven:  A Texan headed south with an Okie under each arm.&quot;  So stand up and be counted! What you be? A texan or an okie?  What's with all those Tornado attractors out there? (Mobile home parks) Any body live in a house? I did my AIT at Ft. Sill and I just LOVED the okie humor in Lawton.  &lt;G&gt;  And don't get me started on Texas.<br>
Doc Del, your turn.  Livin' in Paradise.. up on the side of a mountain.. no neighbors... clear fields of fire.. livin' in a tropical jungle..  HMMMMM  Any reason to be concerned here?  Other than he is so ugly and misshapen that the natives sacrafice virgins to him to keep him up in the hills..  Wow! That don't sound too bad!  Got an extra room?  I'll bring the Spam and mayo!<br>
Let's see, did that cover everyone?  Don't want to leave anyone out.<br>
Oh,yeah.  Cook?  Come play.  Put down the &quot;tude and lighten up. We can talk issues, but to do it all the time gets old. Let's clear the air. Draw each other out and talk without calling each other out.  Passion, thirty years old is difficult.  People recoil everytime a response is posted to your comments and is met with a 9 paragraph response. State it simpler, please. I like reading your stories and I like Ed's poems. I hope this does not offend. I look for brevity. But then that is just me, having posted a nine paragraph response to these people picking on this por ol' Virginia Gentleman! &lt;G&gt;  
